summary: This is a court subpoena issued by the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York to the Sacramento County Clerk/Recorder, commanding their appearance and production of a birth certificate for an unnamed individual in the case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell. The subpoena is signed by U.S. Attorney Audrey Strauss.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell

events.description: The Sacramento County Clerk/Recorder is commanded to appear before the U.S. District Court to testify and produce a birth certificate.

locations: 40 Foley Square, Courtroom 906, Borough of Manhattan, City of New York, New York, Southern District of New York
keyFacts: A subpoena was issued to compel the Sacramento County Clerk/Recorder to produce a birth certificate for an unnamed individual as part of the case against Ghislaine Maxwell.
The subpoena was issued by the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York, signed by U.S. Attorney Audrey Strauss on August 27, 2021.
The document indicates ongoing evidence gathering in the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell (20 Cr. 330) as of late 2021.
